    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-05-09</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-06-29T14:05:08Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends the Energy Employees Occupational Illness Compensation Program Act of 2000 to include within the meaning of the term &#147;member of the Special Exposure Cohort&#148; a Department of Energy employee, Department of Energy contractor employee, or atomic weapons employee who was so employed for a number of work days aggregating at least 250 work days before January 1, 2006, at the Santa Susana Field Laboratory in California.</p><p>Provides that a claim that an individual qualifies for compensation or benefits under such Act shall be considered notwithstanding any denial of any other claim for compensation with respect to such individual.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
